1
00:00:01,635 --> 00:00:05,838
              AMY:
 So, Sheldon, there's something
I've been wanting to talk about.

2
00:00:05,840 --> 00:00:07,673
        But I know it's
   kind of a touchy subject.

3
00:00:07,675 --> 00:00:09,742
Way to narrow it down
to everything.

4
00:00:10,644 --> 00:00:11,877
          What is it?

5
00:00:11,879 --> 00:00:13,379
Well, your birthday's coming up.

6
00:00:13,381 --> 00:00:14,680
        And you've never
      let us celebrate it.

7
00:00:14,682 --> 00:00:16,515
          And I was hoping maybe
             this year we could.

8
00:00:16,517 --> 00:00:19,718
Oh, I suppose that's
a discussion we could have.

9
00:00:24,492 --> 00:00:26,492
      Okay, great, I mean,

10
00:00:26,494 --> 00:00:29,194
     it doesn't have to be
    a big party or anything.

11
00:00:29,196 --> 00:00:31,263
         I was just...

12
00:00:33,667 --> 00:00:35,334
Where'd he go?

13
00:00:35,336 --> 00:00:36,568
        W-Wait a minute.

14
00:00:36,570 --> 00:00:38,837
    You mention his birthday
        and he vanishes?

15
00:00:38,839 --> 00:00:42,041
Well, where's that information
been this whole time?

16
00:00:43,477 --> 00:00:46,979
      ♪ Our whole universe
  was in a hot, dense state ♪

17
00:00:46,981 --> 00:00:50,349
 ♪ Then nearly 14 billion years
ago expansion started... Wait! ♪

18
00:00:50,351 --> 00:00:51,917
  ♪ The Earth began to cool ♪

19
00:00:51,919 --> 00:00:54,553
♪ The autotrophs began to drool,
 Neanderthals developed tools ♪

20
00:00:54,555 --> 00:00:57,189
     ♪ We built the Wall ♪
   ♪<i> We built the pyramids</i> ♪

21
00:00:57,191 --> 00:00:59,825
   ♪ Math, Science, History,
    unraveling the mystery ♪

22
00:00:59,827 --> 00:01:01,760
       ♪ That all started
       with a big bang ♪

23
00:01:01,762 --> 00:01:03,662
           ♪<i> Bang!</i> ♪

24
00:01:12,273 --> 00:01:13,772
       Well, where is he?

25
00:01:13,774 --> 00:01:15,007
Sheldon?

26
00:01:15,009 --> 00:01:16,075
      I'll check his room.

27
00:01:16,077 --> 00:01:17,443
                   Surprise!
(both scream)

28
00:01:17,445 --> 00:01:18,577
                     Oh, my God!

29
00:01:18,579 --> 00:01:20,579
        Just one example

30
00:01:20,581 --> 00:01:23,082
        of how birthdays
        can be terrible.

31
00:01:23,084 --> 00:01:25,517
       Now, can we please

32
00:01:25,519 --> 00:01:26,718
       drop this subject
      and pick a new one?

33
00:01:26,720 --> 00:01:29,288
        Yeah, I suggest
   "how thick can a soup get

34
00:01:29,290 --> 00:01:30,756
   before it becomes a stew?"

35
00:01:30,758 --> 00:01:33,225
     You know, the answer,
      it may surprise you.

36
00:01:33,227 --> 00:01:36,061
   I'm sorry I brought it up.

37
00:01:36,063 --> 00:01:37,362
   Yeah, what is the problem?

38
00:01:37,364 --> 00:01:38,430
   Is it about getting older?

39
00:01:38,432 --> 00:01:40,699
            Please, look at this
                 porcelain skin.

40
00:01:40,701 --> 00:01:43,502
          I'm like a human sink.

41
00:01:44,805 --> 00:01:48,707
But it's the one day a year
that's just all about you.

42
00:01:48,709 --> 00:01:50,709
            One day.
            (laughs)

43
00:01:54,081 --> 00:01:55,214
             Right.

44
00:01:57,284 --> 00:01:59,384
Can you please just tell me why?

45
00:01:59,386 --> 00:02:02,454
                      Fine.

46
00:02:02,456 --> 00:02:04,756
                    As you know,
            I have a twin sister

47
00:02:04,758 --> 00:02:07,126
           with whom I obviously
               share a birthday.

48
00:02:07,128 --> 00:02:09,094
                 Every year we'd
                   have a party.

49
00:02:09,096 --> 00:02:10,796
        No one I invited
        would ever come,

50
00:02:10,798 --> 00:02:11,897
  because they didn't like me.

51
00:02:13,267 --> 00:02:14,733
           I'm sorry.

52
00:02:14,735 --> 00:02:16,068
    Oh, that part wasn't so bad.

53
00:02:16,070 --> 00:02:17,302
     I didn't like them, either.

54
00:02:17,304 --> 00:02:18,937
   But then I'd inevitably spend

55
00:02:18,939 --> 00:02:22,608
    the whole day being tortured
         by my sister's friends.

56
00:02:22,610 --> 00:02:24,510
             Oh, you poor thing.

57
00:02:24,512 --> 00:02:26,745
    When I was six, they told me
  Batman was coming to my party.

58
00:02:26,747 --> 00:02:28,814
                 I waited by the
                 door for hours.

59
00:02:28,816 --> 00:02:30,816
                   Closest thing
                 to Batman I saw

60
00:02:30,818 --> 00:02:32,885
                was when a robin
           flew into the window.

61
00:02:34,788 --> 00:02:37,356
You realize none of those things
would happen now?

62
00:02:37,358 --> 00:02:39,324
       I do, but why do you care

63
00:02:39,326 --> 00:02:41,426
                  if I celebrate
             my birthday at all?

64
00:02:41,428 --> 00:02:44,630
Well, you made
my last birthday so memorable,

65
00:02:44,632 --> 00:02:46,632
I wanted to return the favor.

66
00:02:46,634 --> 00:02:47,633
PENNY:
Yeah, if you had

67
00:02:47,635 --> 00:02:49,134
                a party now, you
          have plenty of friends

68
00:02:49,136 --> 00:02:50,435
        that would love to come.

69
00:02:50,437 --> 00:02:51,937
And we live here,
so we have no choice.

70
00:02:51,939 --> 00:02:53,772
                     Yeah.

71
00:02:55,276 --> 00:02:56,675
                      Very well.

72
00:02:56,677 --> 00:02:58,644
       You may celebrate my life
             by throwing a party

73
00:02:58,646 --> 00:03:01,713
       with cake, presents and a
  shower of admiration and love.

74
00:03:01,715 --> 00:03:03,782
   But then you owe me big-time.

75
00:03:06,353 --> 00:03:08,487
You have any idea
what you're getting

76
00:03:08,489 --> 00:03:09,821
   Sheldon for his birthday?

77
00:03:09,823 --> 00:03:11,890
      He's been fascinated
     with dinosaurs lately.

78
00:03:11,892 --> 00:03:13,458
Maybe we could get him a fossil.

79
00:03:13,460 --> 00:03:15,494
        Well, just don't
     get anything Jurassic.

80
00:03:15,496 --> 00:03:18,797
 He feels like that whole chunk
  of time has gone Hollywood.

81
00:03:20,534 --> 00:03:22,734
       Hey, uh, you know,

82
00:03:22,736 --> 00:03:25,504
      he told a sad story
      about how his sister

83
00:03:25,506 --> 00:03:28,874
tricked him into thinking Batman
    was coming to his party.

84
00:03:28,876 --> 00:03:30,042
         That's funny.

85
00:03:30,044 --> 00:03:31,810
         Let's do that.

86
00:03:33,314 --> 00:03:35,480
   Maybe we could get Batman
      to actually show up.

87
00:03:35,482 --> 00:03:37,983
              You mean, some guy
                 in a lame suit?

88
00:03:37,985 --> 00:03:40,252
       Or a real Batman.
          Hey, Stuart?

89
00:03:40,254 --> 00:03:42,754
Didn't you try to get Adam West
   to do a signing here once?

90
00:03:42,756 --> 00:03:45,390
  Yeah, but there was kind of
     a scheduling conflict.

91
00:03:45,392 --> 00:03:48,193
          He, uh, wanted to know
             when he'd get paid.

92
00:03:48,195 --> 00:03:49,962
        And I wouldn't tell him.

93
00:03:51,732 --> 00:03:53,732
  Can I get his contact info?

94
00:03:53,734 --> 00:03:55,867
                   Sure, uh, but
               just so you know,

95
00:03:55,869 --> 00:03:57,369
            he's kind of a diva.

96
00:03:57,371 --> 00:03:59,238
He is?
                       Oh, yeah.

97
00:03:59,240 --> 00:04:00,339
             Won't take the bus.

98
00:04:00,341 --> 00:04:01,773
    He won't pack his own lunch.

99
00:04:01,775 --> 00:04:04,910
      Won't let you spend
    the night on his couch.

100
00:04:07,281 --> 00:04:10,282
        Okay, so how do you feel
           about party balloons?

101
00:04:10,284 --> 00:04:11,883
    Uh, Mylar balloons, yes.

102
00:04:11,885 --> 00:04:13,619
      Latex balloons, no.

103
00:04:13,621 --> 00:04:15,787
        Water balloons,
    I will jump off the roof

104
00:04:15,789 --> 00:04:17,856
     and aim for your car.

105
00:04:18,759 --> 00:04:20,926
    All right, what about music?

106
00:04:20,928 --> 00:04:22,427
     I enjoy marching bands

107
00:04:22,429 --> 00:04:25,097
  and Tibetan throat singing.

108
00:04:25,099 --> 00:04:26,465
                 No music it is.

109
00:04:27,735 --> 00:04:29,234
What kind of cake
do you like?

110
00:04:29,236 --> 00:04:32,070
 Well, my favorite is chocolate
   with strawberry frosting,

111
00:04:32,072 --> 00:04:33,972
three layers,
and if there's

112
00:04:33,974 --> 00:04:35,907
         writing on it,
  make sure it's not all caps.

113
00:04:35,909 --> 00:04:39,044
    I don't need my dessert
         yelling at me.

114
00:04:41,282 --> 00:04:44,316
        Hey, so what was
  Adam West like on the phone?

115
00:04:44,318 --> 00:04:45,784
         Uh, nice guy.

116
00:04:45,786 --> 00:04:47,452
   But it was a little weird
      to hear Batman say,

117
00:04:47,454 --> 00:04:51,323
    "Don't ring the doorbell
 or my poodles will go crazy."

118
00:04:51,325 --> 00:04:54,259
      You know, Adam West
     is my favorite Batman?

119
00:04:54,261 --> 00:04:55,727
             Well,

120
00:04:55,729 --> 00:04:57,896
           after Michael Keaton,
                  Christian Bale

121
00:04:57,898 --> 00:04:59,998
                and Batman from
                <i> The Lego Movie.</i>

122
00:05:01,502 --> 00:05:02,934
     Don't say that to him.

123
00:05:02,936 --> 00:05:05,103
             What?
  He beat out George Clooney.

124
00:05:05,105 --> 00:05:06,171
           And that's something.

125
00:05:06,173 --> 00:05:08,573
                 Like, I love me
                   some Clooney.

126
00:05:08,575 --> 00:05:10,876
   Don't say that to anyone.

127
00:05:13,147 --> 00:05:15,514
       Thank you so much
    for helping us, Stuart.

128
00:05:15,516 --> 00:05:17,182
                Oh, I-I was just

129
00:05:17,184 --> 00:05:18,817
      glad to be invited.

130
00:05:18,819 --> 00:05:21,787
  To be honest, I don't always
feel like I'm part of the group.

131
00:05:21,789 --> 00:05:23,021
Okay, sweetie,
we're on the clock here.

132
00:05:23,023 --> 00:05:25,657
Can you hate yourself
and frost at the same time?

133
00:05:25,659 --> 00:05:26,992
          (door opens)

134
00:05:26,994 --> 00:05:29,428
Hello, I hope I'm not too early.

135
00:05:29,430 --> 00:05:30,462
    No, no, no. Come on in.

136
00:05:30,464 --> 00:05:32,831
     And how is the radiant
          mommy-to-be?

137
00:05:32,833 --> 00:05:34,433
          Doing great.

138
00:05:34,435 --> 00:05:36,468
       Y-You're pregnant?

139
00:05:36,470 --> 00:05:37,436
                     Yeah.

140
00:05:37,438 --> 00:05:39,504
     Sounds like something

141
00:05:39,506 --> 00:05:42,341
     a member of the group
          might know.

142
00:05:42,343 --> 00:05:43,675
Yeah, birthday party first.

143
00:05:43,677 --> 00:05:45,577
Pity party later.

144
00:05:48,282 --> 00:05:49,548
         Are you crazy?

145
00:05:49,550 --> 00:05:51,183
 How can you put Michael Keaton

146
00:05:51,185 --> 00:05:53,552
  in front of Christian Bale?

147
00:05:53,554 --> 00:05:55,620
Oh, please.

148
00:05:57,858 --> 00:06:01,226
      Even my poodles know
       Bale's overrated.

149
00:06:01,228 --> 00:06:03,362
           Thank you!

150
00:06:03,364 --> 00:06:05,297
        That's why I say
      Keaton's number one.

151
00:06:05,299 --> 00:06:06,865
       He brought a sense
     of humor to the role.

152
00:06:06,867 --> 00:06:08,900
      Oh, if you're gonna
  factor in a sense of humor,

153
00:06:08,902 --> 00:06:12,070
        then I should be
    at the top of the list.

154
00:06:12,072 --> 00:06:14,873
It should be me,

155
00:06:14,875 --> 00:06:16,074
Keaton, Kilmer,

156
00:06:16,076 --> 00:06:17,876
          Lego, Bale,

157
00:06:17,878 --> 00:06:19,945
  and that pretty boy Clooney.

158
00:06:21,582 --> 00:06:23,815
                   Really?

159
00:06:23,817 --> 00:06:25,317
     You're ahead of Bale?

160
00:06:25,319 --> 00:06:27,386
    The man who personified
           the words,

161
00:06:27,388 --> 00:06:30,255
         (deep voice):
         "I'm Batman."

162
00:06:30,257 --> 00:06:32,023
 I never had to say I'm Batman.

163
00:06:32,025 --> 00:06:33,024
          I showed up.

164
00:06:33,026 --> 00:06:35,427
   People knew I was Batman.

165
00:06:36,930 --> 00:06:39,164
Everywhere I went--
on the TV show,

166
00:06:39,166 --> 00:06:40,399
mall openings...

167
00:06:40,401 --> 00:06:43,468
    Julie Newmar's bungalow.

168
00:06:46,206 --> 00:06:48,607
I'm sold-- you're ahead of Bale.

169
00:06:49,943 --> 00:06:52,377
There's another reason
I should be higher on the list.

170
00:06:52,379 --> 00:06:54,045
All those other guys

171
00:06:54,047 --> 00:06:57,082
       had muscles built
      into their costumes.

172
00:06:57,084 --> 00:06:59,251
    All I had in my Batsuit

173
00:06:59,253 --> 00:07:03,088
    was 100%, grade-A West.

174
00:07:05,959 --> 00:07:08,593
        Can we just all agree
    we're worried about Affleck?

175
00:07:08,595 --> 00:07:10,495
                           Sure.
      Yeah, of course.

176
00:07:12,099 --> 00:07:13,932
       What's an Affleck?

177
00:07:17,104 --> 00:07:19,738
         Is there a reason I had
      to leave my own apartment?

178
00:07:19,740 --> 00:07:21,306
         Well, I think
  they just want you to see it

179
00:07:21,308 --> 00:07:23,074
       for the first time
         all decorated.

180
00:07:23,076 --> 00:07:26,611
       But who's gonna tell them
         they're doing it wrong?

181
00:07:26,613 --> 00:07:29,948
 Well, I'm... I'm sure they'll
   ask you to give a speech,

182
00:07:29,950 --> 00:07:32,484
        and that's when
  you just tear 'em a new one.

183
00:07:32,486 --> 00:07:35,420
Have to say, you...

184
00:07:35,422 --> 00:07:37,322
 you do look good in that suit.

185
00:07:37,324 --> 00:07:38,824
         Oh. Thank you.

186
00:07:38,826 --> 00:07:41,126
    Maybe later I'll, uh...

187
00:07:41,128 --> 00:07:44,529
         get to see you
     in your birthday suit.

188
00:07:46,967 --> 00:07:49,468
                  But this<i> is</i> my
                  birthday suit.

189
00:07:51,138 --> 00:07:53,705
    Are you having a stroke?

190
00:07:55,142 --> 00:07:56,475
Because that's the kind of thing

191
00:07:56,477 --> 00:07:57,809
        that just ruins
       a birthday party.

192
00:08:00,447 --> 00:08:02,981
   So, Mother, I'm surprised
     you came all this way

193
00:08:02,983 --> 00:08:04,149
    for Sheldon's birthday.

194
00:08:04,151 --> 00:08:05,016
      Oh, I was happy to.

195
00:08:05,018 --> 00:08:07,018
    He did come to my 60th.

196
00:08:07,020 --> 00:08:11,022
        Oh. You had a party
           for your 60th?

197
00:08:11,024 --> 00:08:13,191
Oh, I wouldn't call it a party.

198
00:08:13,193 --> 00:08:15,227
   Just a few close friends.

199
00:08:16,663 --> 00:08:18,430
  And your sister and brother.

200
00:08:21,034 --> 00:08:23,301
You know, to be fair,
we did get married in Vegas

201
00:08:23,303 --> 00:08:24,436
and didn't invite her.

202
00:08:24,438 --> 00:08:27,072
   And I never did thank you
        for that, dear.

203
00:08:30,043 --> 00:08:31,776
        (ringtone plays)
AMY:
Oh.

204
00:08:31,778 --> 00:08:34,846
Penny says everyone's there.
Are you ready?

205
00:08:34,848 --> 00:08:37,082
      (takes deep breath)
             I am.

206
00:08:44,791 --> 00:08:47,125
   Oh. Wait.
              Are you all right?

207
00:08:47,127 --> 00:08:49,828
         No, I just...
  I got a little light-headed.

208
00:08:49,830 --> 00:08:51,196
  Oh, d-do you need a minute?

209
00:08:51,198 --> 00:08:53,298
      (exhales)
         No.

210
00:08:53,300 --> 00:08:55,700
No, if I can walk
past that pet shop

211
00:08:55,702 --> 00:08:59,070
with the parrot in the window,
I suppose I can do this.

212
00:09:04,011 --> 00:09:06,578
            OTHERS:
        Happy birthday!

213
00:09:06,580 --> 00:09:08,313
      (whooping, clapping)

214
00:09:08,315 --> 00:09:09,581
            Speech! Speech!

215
00:09:10,551 --> 00:09:12,551
               Come on, Sheldon,
                  say something.

216
00:09:12,553 --> 00:09:13,852
        Uh, um...

217
00:09:13,854 --> 00:09:16,221
uh, thank you all
so much for coming.

218
00:09:16,223 --> 00:09:17,522
Uh, Beverly.

219
00:09:17,524 --> 00:09:19,558
Wil Wheaton.

220
00:09:19,560 --> 00:09:21,993
Adam West,
for some reason.

221
00:09:23,497 --> 00:09:26,064
      Batman finally came
         to your party.

222
00:09:26,066 --> 00:09:28,833
    Happy birthday, Sherman.

223
00:09:32,239 --> 00:09:33,505
SHELDON:
Thank you.

224
00:09:33,507 --> 00:09:35,373
This is all so thoughtful.

225
00:09:35,375 --> 00:09:38,109
  (heartbeat thumping loudly)

226
00:09:44,251 --> 00:09:45,784
           (panting):
           Excuse me.

227
00:09:53,126 --> 00:09:55,026
   I still get paid, don't I?

228
00:10:01,802 --> 00:10:04,135
          Okay, I'd better go in
          there and talk to him.

229
00:10:04,137 --> 00:10:06,104
     Well, don't you think
 I'm the one who should go in?

230
00:10:06,106 --> 00:10:08,974
   No offense, but I've known
  the guy a really long time.

231
00:10:08,976 --> 00:10:10,875
Well, I've, you know,

232
00:10:10,877 --> 00:10:13,345
   seen him without pants on.

233
00:10:14,381 --> 00:10:17,549
       Again, no offense,
         but so have I.

234
00:10:17,551 --> 00:10:19,784
       Well, he's seen me
       without pants on.

235
00:10:19,786 --> 00:10:20,752
          Again, no...

236
00:10:20,754 --> 00:10:22,821
   Okay, this is ridiculous.

237
00:10:24,257 --> 00:10:26,091
           (knocking)

238
00:10:26,093 --> 00:10:26,958
Sheldon?

239
00:10:26,960 --> 00:10:27,959
Can I come in?

240
00:10:27,961 --> 00:10:29,260
            (sighs)

241
00:10:29,262 --> 00:10:32,097
 How do you know I'm not using
        the facilities?

242
00:10:32,099 --> 00:10:34,799
   Because you e-mail me your
 bathroom schedule once a week,

243
00:10:34,801 --> 00:10:36,134
          even though
   I've clicked unsubscribe,

244
00:10:36,136 --> 00:10:37,669
    like, a thousand times.

245
00:10:44,111 --> 00:10:45,677
So...

246
00:10:45,679 --> 00:10:47,245
        what's going on?

247
00:10:47,247 --> 00:10:48,780
         I don't know.

248
00:10:48,782 --> 00:10:50,482
  I-I looked around the room,

249
00:10:50,484 --> 00:10:52,517
    and I saw all the faces
       and the presents,

250
00:10:52,519 --> 00:10:54,853
and it... it was just too much.

251
00:10:56,256 --> 00:10:57,355
          I get that.

252
00:10:59,826 --> 00:11:02,327
Hey, you want to just bring
a few people in here?

253
00:11:02,329 --> 00:11:04,162
You know,
Wil Wheaton in the bathtub,

254
00:11:04,164 --> 00:11:06,464
Batman on the toilet.

255
00:11:06,466 --> 00:11:08,433
         It'll be like
  the weirdest Comic-Con ever.

256
00:11:11,505 --> 00:11:13,772
  I know that you worked hard
     to put this together.

257
00:11:13,774 --> 00:11:15,140
   I'm sorry I'm ruining it.

258
00:11:15,142 --> 00:11:16,541
Oh, pl...
You're not ruining it.

259
00:11:16,543 --> 00:11:18,510
      Look, at some point,
  Raj will try to get everyone

260
00:11:18,512 --> 00:11:19,844
   to do the Electric Slide.

261
00:11:19,846 --> 00:11:21,346
    Now, that will ruin it.

262
00:11:23,283 --> 00:11:25,550
         I don't think
    I can go back out there.

263
00:11:26,486 --> 00:11:28,253
          That's fine.

264
00:11:39,566 --> 00:11:42,167
You know, I hate that
your sister and her friends

265
00:11:42,169 --> 00:11:44,302
used to torture you.

266
00:11:44,304 --> 00:11:46,237
But what I hate even more

267
00:11:46,239 --> 00:11:49,474
is, if I was there,
I would have tortured you, too.

268
00:11:51,978 --> 00:11:54,846
         Based on this pep talk,
  I'd say you're still doing it.

269
00:11:54,848 --> 00:11:57,215
(scoffs)
My point is,

270
00:11:57,217 --> 00:11:59,184
there was a time I never
would've been friends

271
00:11:59,186 --> 00:12:01,386
with someone like you,
and now...

272
00:12:01,388 --> 00:12:03,321
you are one
of my favorite people.

273
00:12:03,323 --> 00:12:05,523
So, if what you need is

274
00:12:05,525 --> 00:12:08,326
to spend your birthday
in a bathroom,

275
00:12:08,328 --> 00:12:11,329
I'm happy to do it with you.

276
00:12:13,166 --> 00:12:15,233
             Well, everyone will
                think I'm weird.

277
00:12:22,209 --> 00:12:24,476
Sweetie, you are weird.

278
00:12:25,746 --> 00:12:27,612
Everyone knows you're weird,

279
00:12:27,614 --> 00:12:29,013
but they're all still here

280
00:12:29,015 --> 00:12:31,449
because they care
about you so much.

281
00:12:31,451 --> 00:12:32,717
           (knocking)

