00:12:33,854 --> 00:12:35,386
Some of us need
to check our hair

284
00:12:35,388 --> 00:12:38,156
because we might have a shot
with Leonard's mother.

285
00:12:41,528 --> 00:12:43,361
Leonard.
              Hey.

286
00:12:43,363 --> 00:12:44,729
It's been a while.

287
00:12:44,731 --> 00:12:45,897
                         Leslie.

288
00:12:45,899 --> 00:12:47,432
        I can't remember
    the last time we talked.

289
00:12:47,434 --> 00:12:49,167
      So much has changed.

290
00:12:50,871 --> 00:12:53,138
            Has it?

291
00:12:54,708 --> 00:12:56,641
         Yeah, uh, um,
    Penny and I got married.

292
00:12:56,643 --> 00:12:58,209
     Wow, congratulations.

293
00:12:58,211 --> 00:12:59,377
      You know, actually,

294
00:12:59,379 --> 00:13:01,246
   I thought you'd be living
     with Sheldon forever.

295
00:13:01,248 --> 00:13:02,981
         Yeah, well...

296
00:13:04,885 --> 00:13:06,017
      Don't be a stranger.

297
00:13:07,254 --> 00:13:09,220
        Okay, everybody,

298
00:13:09,222 --> 00:13:10,388
Sheldon is gonna come back out,

299
00:13:10,390 --> 00:13:11,756
          but I think
   he's a little embarrassed,

300
00:13:11,758 --> 00:13:14,259
        so let's all be
       extra nice, okay?

301
00:13:14,261 --> 00:13:15,760
What are you
looking at me for?

302
00:13:15,762 --> 00:13:17,295
I'm a saint. (chuckles)

303
00:13:17,297 --> 00:13:19,164
But a sinner in the sack.

304
00:13:23,303 --> 00:13:24,469
        Hello, everyone.

305
00:13:24,471 --> 00:13:25,637
             I-I...

306
00:13:25,639 --> 00:13:27,505
     I'd like to apologize
        for my behavior.

307
00:13:27,507 --> 00:13:30,441
      I hope it hasn't put
     a damper on the party.

308
00:13:30,443 --> 00:13:32,310
       So, just, please,
       enjoy yourselves.

309
00:13:32,312 --> 00:13:33,478
              That's good.

310
00:13:33,480 --> 00:13:36,915
    (party chatter resumes)

311
00:13:36,917 --> 00:13:39,317
             Oh, this is quickly
            getting out of hand.

312
00:13:39,319 --> 00:13:41,419
If I may,

313
00:13:41,421 --> 00:13:43,588
I-I'd like to propose a toast.

314
00:13:43,590 --> 00:13:46,024
Um, thank you all
for coming tonight.

315
00:13:46,026 --> 00:13:47,258
I know it's customary

316
00:13:47,260 --> 00:13:50,161
      for the birthday boy
      to receive presents,

317
00:13:50,163 --> 00:13:52,363
     but I feel like I got
       the greatest gift

318
00:13:52,365 --> 00:13:53,665
      the day he was born.

319
00:13:53,667 --> 00:13:54,699
              ALL:
              Aw.

320
00:13:54,701 --> 00:13:56,701
                     Hear, hear.
KOOTHRAPPALI:
Cheers.

321
00:13:56,703 --> 00:13:59,137
     Amy, that was lovely.

322
00:13:59,139 --> 00:14:00,471
                       You know,

323
00:14:00,473 --> 00:14:01,472
                    this is fun.

324
00:14:01,474 --> 00:14:02,774
                  Let's do more.

325
00:14:02,776 --> 00:14:05,143
      Someone else say something
             wonderful about me.

326
00:14:05,145 --> 00:14:07,512
          Sheldon,
 I don't think everyone...

327
00:14:07,514 --> 00:14:09,380
       Wolowitz, perfect.
  Everyone listen to Wolowitz.

328
00:14:10,650 --> 00:14:12,383
Okay, then, uh, (clears throat)

329
00:14:12,385 --> 00:14:14,452
      Sheldon, (chuckles)

330
00:14:14,454 --> 00:14:15,954
     we've known each other
          a long time.

331
00:14:15,956 --> 00:14:19,324
      And it is a pleasure
        to work with you

332
00:14:19,326 --> 00:14:21,025
    and call you my friend.

333
00:14:21,027 --> 00:14:22,560
 Little generic. Keep thinking.
       We'll circle back.

334
00:14:22,562 --> 00:14:24,062
                Wil Wheaton, go.

335
00:14:25,699 --> 00:14:29,000
 Sheldon, I know that we've had
       our ups and downs,

336
00:14:29,002 --> 00:14:31,135
but I can honestly say

337
00:14:31,137 --> 00:14:32,503
        that my life is
    so much more interesting

338
00:14:32,505 --> 00:14:33,805
     because you are in it.

339
00:14:33,807 --> 00:14:37,408
We may have met because
you are a fan of<i> Star Trek.</i>

340
00:14:37,410 --> 00:14:39,711
       But I have become
    a fan of Sheldon Cooper.

341
00:14:39,713 --> 00:14:41,412
Live long and prosper,
buddy.

342
00:14:41,414 --> 00:14:42,547
      And happy birthday.

343
00:14:42,549 --> 00:14:43,815
              ALL:
            Cheers.

344
00:14:43,817 --> 00:14:46,150
That's how you do it, Wolowitz.

345
00:14:46,152 --> 00:14:48,186
Now you see

346
00:14:48,188 --> 00:14:49,621
why he's famous and you're not.

347
00:14:52,025 --> 00:14:53,524
                        Sheldon,

348
00:14:53,526 --> 00:14:56,160
    I know the future holds
     great things for you,

349
00:14:56,162 --> 00:14:58,763
  and we all can't wait to see
         what they are.

350
00:14:58,765 --> 00:15:01,099
     Happy birthday, dear.

351
00:15:01,101 --> 00:15:02,901
              ALL:
            Cheers.

352
00:15:02,903 --> 00:15:04,569
Someone call Animal Control.

