00:15:24,891 --> 00:15:26,591
   And it was Sheldon Cooper who
      said "Let's speed this up.

362
00:15:26,593 --> 00:15:28,927
  A lot of people want to talk."

363
00:15:28,929 --> 00:15:31,796
Uh, in the past, I would've said
      something obnoxious,

364
00:15:31,798 --> 00:15:34,065
like, "Happy birthday, dumbass."

365
00:15:34,067 --> 00:15:36,200
But I'm not gonna do it.

366
00:15:36,202 --> 00:15:37,902
You and I have both grown a lot,

367
00:15:37,904 --> 00:15:40,538
     and it's just so nice
     to see you all again.

368
00:15:40,540 --> 00:15:41,773
So...

369
00:15:41,775 --> 00:15:43,308
    happy birthday, Sheldon.

370
00:15:43,310 --> 00:15:44,442
              Oh.

371
00:15:44,444 --> 00:15:46,477
Oh, now, you know I hate change.
            Say it.

372
00:15:46,479 --> 00:15:48,279
    Happy birthday, dumbass!

373
00:15:48,281 --> 00:15:50,048
           (cheering)

374
00:15:50,050 --> 00:15:51,649
Happy birthday, young man.

375
00:15:51,651 --> 00:15:55,320
And if any of you have enjoyed
seeing me here today,

376
00:15:55,322 --> 00:15:57,922
       I'm also available
        for Comic-Cons,

377
00:15:57,924 --> 00:16:01,059
       bachelor parties,
        bar mitzvahs...

378
00:16:01,061 --> 00:16:04,462
I can't think of anything to say
 that hasn't already been said.

379
00:16:04,464 --> 00:16:06,798
  So, here's to you, Sheldon.

380
00:16:06,800 --> 00:16:08,166
Hear, hear.
          Hear, hear.

381
00:16:08,168 --> 00:16:09,500
     Thank you, Bernadette.

382
00:16:09,502 --> 00:16:10,568
       That was perfect.

383
00:16:10,570 --> 00:16:14,305
What? You gotta be kidding me?

384
00:16:14,307 --> 00:16:16,574
             Sheldon, we've been
               together so long,

385
00:16:16,576 --> 00:16:19,310
  it's hard to remember a time
    you weren't in my life.

386
00:16:19,312 --> 00:16:20,645
     And believe me, I try.

387
00:16:20,647 --> 00:16:22,647
(laughter)

388
00:16:22,649 --> 00:16:23,815
       You make me laugh.

389
00:16:23,817 --> 00:16:26,117
You make me a better scientist.

390
00:16:26,119 --> 00:16:27,585
              You make me crazy.

391
00:16:27,587 --> 00:16:29,253
     You're more than just
          my roommate,

392
00:16:29,255 --> 00:16:30,722
       you're my brother.

393
00:16:31,624 --> 00:16:32,790
           Thank you.

394
00:16:32,792 --> 00:16:34,325
     Happy birthday, buddy.

395
00:16:34,327 --> 00:16:35,893
              ALL:
            Cheers.

396
00:16:36,997 --> 00:16:38,863
                      Thank you.
        That-that was wonderful.

